sql:
SELECT COUNT(*) AS pending_reset_requests
FROM password_resets
WHERE is_used = 0;

SELECT COUNT(user_id) AS admin_user_count
FROM user_roles
WHERE role_id = (SELECT role_id FROM roles WHERE role_name = 'admin');

SELECT user_id
FROM activity_logs
WHERE activity_timestamp = (SELECT MAX(activity_timestamp) FROM activity_logs);

external_knowledge:
Active users refer to those with a status of 'active' in the database; 
Recent activity refers to the activity with the most recent timestamp for each user; 
Multiple privileges refer to having more than one permission.

sql:
SELECT COUNT(*) AS login_count
FROM activity_logs
WHERE user_id = 1 AND activity_type = 'login';
